            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Nice writeup! Not obvious how to design this. \n\nFor #38744, `all=true` wouldn't help because both `.tar.gz` and `.tar` are expected extensions.\n\nMaybe `max=n` with multiple return values?\n\n```lua\n  local path = url_path(url)\n  -- Example: path=\"foo.tar.gz\"\n  local ext1, ext2 = vim.fs.ext(path, { max=2 })\n  --    ^tar  ^tar.gz\n  if ext2 and archive_patterns[ext2] then\n    ...\n  elseif ext1 and archive_patterns[ext1] then\n    ...\n  end\n```\n\n",
