            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> Elegant\" can also mean \"minimal\" and \"composable\" ;)\n\nDefinitely! Not trying to argue with that :) \n\n> The \"hard part\" is robustly(!) extracting the extensions\n\nTrue, but `vim.fs.ext()` is only a thin wrapper around `fnamemodify`, which seems tried-and-tested enough to handle these cases. Implementation-wise we would supply the `:e` modifier multiple times to get the extensions. If that doesn't work for a specific case, it's a fnamemodify bug. ",
